docs.title: Native Clustering
docs.description: Native Clustering provides a basic clustering mechanism suitable for single node deployment or smaller clustered deployments. When running Teraslice in it's most simple form, on a single computer, you're using a single node native cluster.

docs.title: Teraslice Configuration
docs.description: Teraslice configuration is provided via a YAML configuration file. This file will typically have 2 sections.

docs.title: Contributing
docs.description: Pull requests are welcome. For major changes, please open an issue first to discuss what you would like to change.

docs.title: Kubernetes
docs.description: Teraslice Kubernetes End-to-End Test Suite and Development Environment

docs.title: Releases
docs.description: A Teraslice "release" is not just the teraslice package alone but a set of version locked packages that work together with teraslice. This is important to note since the packages can change and be released often, but a release undergoes QA. Each release should be attached to a Github Milestone and all issues "fixed" since the previous release should be linked to that Milestone.

docs.title: Tests
docs.description: Note: elasticseach 6 is required for running the tests

docs.title: Getting Started
docs.description: Teraslice is written in Node.js and has been tested on Linux and Mac OS X.

docs.title: Configuration
docs.description: A job configuration is the main way a Teraslice user describes the processing they want done. This page provides a detailed description of the configurations available for a job.

docs.title: Data Entities
docs.description: A DataEntity is wrapper for data that can hold additional metadata properties without mutating the original data.

docs.title: Dead Letter Queue
docs.description: This API available to any operation running in the WorkerContext for putting invalid records or data. This API is useful for placing records that were not formatted correctly or were unserializable.

docs.title: Development
docs.description: When developing on an operation you'll need to be aware of three packages.

docs.title: Jobs Overview
docs.description: Teraslice Jobs are application specific distributed extract, transform, load (ETL) pipelines.

docs.title: Slices
docs.description: Slices are like heartbeats within teraslice, each heartbeat tracks metadata around the work being down.

docs.title: Testing
docs.description: WIP: for now checkout the documentation in teraslice-test-harness.

docs.title: Types of Operations
docs.description: Operations within Teraslice Job are designed to read, transform, write, or monitor data within a Teraslice job.

docs.title: JSON APIs
docs.description: Default endpoint in development is localhost:5678.

docs.title: TXT APIs
docs.description: The txt APIs provide more human readable and script friendly API endpoints for common information requests.

docs.title: Overview
docs.description: The master publishes a REST style API on port 5678.

docs.title: Overview
docs.description: Teraslice provides scalable data processing pipelines implemented using components written in JavaScript. It uses a distributed model to spread work across a cluster of computers and can easily process millions of records per second.

docs.title: Packages
docs.description: Teraslice is a monorepo made up of many packages. Packages that have been deprecated or are no longer recommended for use live under "Legacy". Packages that are not designed to be used outside of teraslice repo are under "Internal".
